I"Ç<h3 id="hamilton-jacobi-theory">Hamilton Jacobi Theory</h3>

<p>In this section, we will introduce Hamilton Jacobi theory. Consider the action $S$:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">S[\textbf{q}] = \int_{t_1}^{t_2}\mathcal{L}(\textbf{q},\dot{\textbf{q}},t) dt</script>

<p>Clearly, $S$ is a <em>functional</em> of the <em>functions</em> $q_1,q_2,\dots,q_n$. However, it can also be thought of as a function of variables $q_1,q_2,\dots,q_n$.</p>

